SIMPLE: reconcentrado
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reconcentrado
<hw>Re*con`cen*tra"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.,
p.p. of <ets>reconcentrar</ets> to inclose, to reconcentrate.]</ety>
<def>Lit., one who has been reconcentrated; specif., in Cuba, the
Philippines, etc., during the revolution of 1895-98, one of the rural
noncombatants who were concentrated by the military authorities in areas
surrounding the fortified towns, and later were reconcentrated in the
smaller limits of the towns themselves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reconcentrate</ent>⟦br⟧
